        bodyEn: '''Horus's hidden years in the Chemmis marshes formed an essential bridge to the next chapter of Egyptian mythology: the long struggle to reclaim the throne seized by Set. Isis, through her devotion, cunning, and mastery of magic, not only succeeded in symbolically reviving Osiris as ruler of the afterlife but also ensured that the rightful royal line survived through Horus. This story cemented Isis's role as the most revered mother goddess and protector in ancient Egypt, worshipped at great temples such as Philae well into the Greco-Roman period. As Horus grew to manhood in hiding, he inherited both the right and the duty to demand justice for his father's death before the tribunal of the gods.''',
